definition: Possession of artifacts (either mystical in nature or quite ordinary) that can be both technological or magical. i.e. Batman
i.e. Iron Man
Possession of artifacts (either mystical in nature or quite ordinary) that can be both technological or magical. i.e. Thor
i.e. Batman (Bruce Wayne)
Ability to fly. i.e. Superman
Ability to generate and control pheromones, which may affect emotional and physical states such as inducing sleep, fear, happiness, and pleasure. i.e. Spider Woman
Ability to duplicate oneself. i.e. Madrox
Ability to control one's own hair. i.e. Medusa
Ability to control or generate magnetic fields. i.e. Magneto
Ability to expel various forms of energy from the body. i.e. Starfire
Ability to generate, manipulate or have immunity to toxic radiation. i.e. Starfire
Ability to project powerful fields of manipulated energy which protect the user and allies from harm, to capture or knock out foes. i.e. Green Lantern
Ability to control, generate or absorb electricity. i.e. Storm
Ability to alter or deceive the perceptions of another. i.e. Lady Mastermind
Ability to increase or decrease one's size. i.e. Giganta
Usually cosmic beings or those who have received their powers from divine beings. i.e. Galactus
Ability to control or influence the natural world including events, objects, people, and physical phenomena through mystical, paranormal or supernatural means. i.e. Dr. Strange
Ability to travel back and forth through time. i.e. Forge
Ability to control, generate or absorb water. i.e. Meggan
Ability to accelerate the growth of, control or animate plant life. i.e. Poison Ivy
